Now I have enough data to provide a comprehensive answer. Here are all the patterns found:

---

## Pattern Examples Found

---

### 1. Conditional Layout Rendering

**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/layout.tsx:42-84`

The only layout in `apps/app/src/app/(app)/` that performs a server-side conditional check is `[slug]/layout.tsx`. It does so via early exits (`notFound()` and `redirect()`) before rendering any JSX — it never renders two different UIs from the same layout:

```tsx
export default async function OrgLayout({ children, params }: OrgLayoutProps) {
  const { slug } = await params;

  let org: { id: string } | null = null;
  try {
    const access = await requireOrgAccess(slug);
    org = { id: access.org.id };
  } catch (error) {
    log.debug("[org-layout] access denied", { slug, error: parseError(error) });
    notFound();  // <-- early exit 1
  }

  // Check GitHub binding — redirect to bind page if missing
  const binding = await getGitHubBinding(org.id);
  if (!binding || binding.status !== "active") {
    redirect(`/account/teams/new/bind?slug=${slug}` as Route);  // <-- early exit 2
  }

  return (
    <HydrateClient>
      <SidebarProvider>...</SidebarProvider>
    </HydrateClient>
  );
}
```

**Key aspects**:
- Guard checks run sequentially at the top before any JSX
- Both guards use Next.js primitives (`notFound()`, `redirect()`) not conditional JSX branches
- No conditional rendering of "setup UI vs. real UI" within the layout itself — the redirect goes to a completely separate page (`/account/teams/new/bind`)
- `HydrateClient` wraps the full layout return (no prefetch calls in this layout)

The redirect destination (`/account/teams/new/bind`) is a standalone client page that handles the setup UI. That page lives at:
`/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/app/(app)/(user)/(pending-allowed)/account/teams/new/bind/page.tsx`

No other layout under `apps/app/src/app/(app)/` performs conditional server-side checks. The `(manage)/layout.tsx`, `(user)/layout.tsx`, and `settings/layout.tsx` all render unconditionally.

---

### 2. BroadcastChannel Usage

**Channel name**: `"oauth-connections"` — used everywhere without variation.

**Sender side** — popup pages post and immediately close the channel:

`/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/app/(providers)/provider/github/connected/page.tsx:11-18`
```tsx
const channel = new BroadcastChannel("oauth-connections");
if (error) {
  channel.postMessage({ type: "github_error", reason: error });
} else {
  channel.postMessage({ type: "github_connected" });
}
channel.close();
```

`/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/app/(providers)/provider/sentry/connected/page.tsx:17-19`
```tsx
const channel = new BroadcastChannel("oauth-connections");
channel.postMessage({ type: "sentry_connected" });
channel.close();
```

Same pattern in `/vercel/connected/page.tsx` (`vercel_connected`) and `/linear/connected/page.tsx` (`linear_connected`).

**Receiver side** — listeners keep the channel open for the component lifetime:

`/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/hooks/use-oauth-popup.ts:69-98`
```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  const channel = new BroadcastChannel("oauth-connections");
  channel.onmessage = (event: MessageEvent) => {
    if ((event.data as { type?: string }).type === resolvedMessageType) {
      invalidateAll();
    }
  };
  // ...
  return () => {
    channel.close();
    // ...
  };
}, [invalidateAll, resolvedMessageType]);
```

**Error-only receiver** at `bind/page.tsx:24-35` listens selectively for `github_error` type to surface an error state, distinct from the success-invalidation pattern in `use-oauth-popup`.

**Message type naming convention**: `{provider}_{event}` — e.g. `github_connected`, `github_error`, `sentry_connected`, `vercel_connected`, `linear_connected`.

All senders also call `window.opener.postMessage()` as a fallback immediately after the BroadcastChannel post.

---

### 3. `useOAuthPopup` Hook Usage

**Defined in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/hooks/use-oauth-popup.ts:26`

**Interface**:
```tsx
interface UseOAuthPopupOptions {
  provider: ProviderSlug;
  queryKeysToInvalidate: readonly (readonly unknown[])[];
  messageType?: string;        // defaults to `${provider}_connected`
  popupWindowName?: string;    // defaults to `${provider}-install`
  onSuccess?: () => void;
  errorMessage?: string;
}
```

**Usage 1 — `bind/page.tsx`** (`/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/app/(app)/(user)/(pending-allowed)/account/teams/new/bind/page.tsx:37-48`):
```tsx
const { handleConnect, isConnecting } = useOAuthPopup({
  provider: "github",
  queryKeysToInvalidate: [
    trpc.githubBinding.get.queryKey(),
    trpc.connections.generic.listInstallations.queryKey(),
  ],
  onSuccess: () => {
    if (slug) {
      router.push(`/${slug}`);
    }
  },
});
```

**Usage 2 — `provider-source-item.tsx`** (`/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/(manage)/sources/new/_components/provider-source-item.tsx:63-72`):
```tsx
const { handleConnect: connectOAuth, isConnecting, openCustomUrl } = useOAuthPopup({
  provider,
  queryKeysToInvalidate: [
    listInstallationsOpts.queryKey,
    ["connections", "generic", "listResources"],
  ],
  onSuccess: () => {
    preferNewestRef.current = true;
  },
});
```

`provider-source-item.tsx` also uses the `openCustomUrl` return value to build a GitHub-specific install URL with a custom `state` parameter.

---

### 4. Status Indicator Pattern (Amber dot / Circle icon)

**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/(manage)/sources/_components/installed-sources.tsx:232-243`

```tsx
<Circle
  className={cn(
    "h-2 w-2 shrink-0 fill-current",
    isAwaitingConfig ? "text-amber-500" : "text-green-500"
  )}
/>
```

The `Circle` icon from `lucide-react` is used with `fill-current` so it renders as a filled dot. `text-amber-500` = warning/awaiting config, `text-green-500` = active/healthy.

**Amber warning banner** (collapsed content, same file, lines 264-285):
```tsx
<div className="mx-4 mb-3 rounded-md border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-2 dark:border-amber-800 dark:bg-amber-950/30">
  <div className="flex items-start gap-2">
    <AlertTriangle className="mt-0.5 h-3.5 w-3.5 shrink-0 text-amber-600" />
    <div className="flex-1 text-xs">
      <p className="font-medium text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-200">
        Configuration Required
      </p>
      <p className="mt-0.5 text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300">...</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

Uses `border-amber-200 bg-amber-50` (light) / `dark:border-amber-800 dark:bg-amber-950/30` (dark), with `AlertTriangle` from lucide-react.

---

